1
00:00:07,018 --> 00:00:11,455
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,523 --> 00:00:15,050
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:15,126 --> 00:00:18,562
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:22,225
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:25,565
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,637 --> 00:00:27,571
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,374 --> 00:00:32,309
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,377 --> 00:00:36,177
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,581 --> 00:00:43,419
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,655 --> 00:00:50,720
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:51,029 --> 00:00:57,161
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,302 --> 00:01:01,568
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,639 --> 00:01:05,234
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,310 --> 00:01:08,643
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,713 --> 00:01:12,342
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,417 --> 00:01:16,012
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:16,087 --> 00:01:19,579
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,657 --> 00:01:23,115
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,328 --> 00:01:27,424
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:37,553 --> 00:01:39,521
- Good bye, Sensei.
- Yay! School's out!

21
00:01:39,788 --> 00:01:41,688
Good bye, Iruka Sensei!

22
00:01:41,991 --> 00:01:43,015
Good bye!

23
00:01:43,192 --> 00:01:47,686
Make sure you practice what
I taught you today, Transform Jutsu!

24
00:01:48,297 --> 00:01:53,792
And tell your family about tomorrow's
inauguration for the Fifth Hokage!

25
00:01:54,236 --> 00:01:55,567
- Okay!
- Okay.

26
00:01:59,274 --> 00:02:00,241
Konohamaru!

27
00:02:00,843 --> 00:02:03,209
What is it, Iruka Sensei?

28
00:02:03,545 --> 00:02:05,706
Well... it's all right.

29
00:02:06,348 --> 00:02:07,576
See you tomorrow!

30
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:10,209
Okay... Goodbye, Iruka Sensei!

31
00:02:13,389 --> 00:02:15,323
<i>It looks like he got over it.</i>

32
00:02:19,728 --> 00:02:20,695
Hey, Lee!

33
00:02:22,931 --> 00:02:24,262
On your way back from rehabilitation?

34
00:02:25,067 --> 00:02:26,364
Um... yes...

35
00:02:26,935 --> 00:02:28,459
I hope you get better soon.

36
00:02:30,606 --> 00:02:31,800
Thank you very much.

37
00:02:48,223 --> 00:02:51,158
<i>To activate each and</i>
<i>every cell all at once...</i>

38
00:02:52,461 --> 00:02:54,224
<i>If it were just one by one,</i>
<i>it'd be a snap,</i>

39
00:02:54,296 --> 00:02:56,230
<i>but all of them together</i>
<i>is gonna be tough.</i>

40
00:02:57,466 --> 00:02:58,490
<i>Still...</i>

41
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:28,623
<i>The Leaf Village is</i>
<i>in great trouble right now,</i>

42
00:03:28,697 --> 00:03:30,892
<i>so we must do our best!</i>

43
00:03:32,034 --> 00:03:36,164
<i>I think if you had Lady Tsunade take</i>
<i>a look, you'd get better very quickly.</i>

44
00:03:37,139 --> 00:03:40,165
<i>It's better that you give up being</i>
<i>a Shinobi and look for a different path.</i>

45
00:03:46,582 --> 00:03:52,350
<i>Sensei and Student.</i>
<i>The Bond of the Shinobi</i>

46
00:03:59,228 --> 00:04:00,718
Clone Jutsu!

47
00:04:06,668 --> 00:04:08,158
Transformation Jutsu!

48
00:04:14,476 --> 00:04:15,465
Hey, young kid...

49
00:04:19,882 --> 00:04:22,680
The medal of youth is one of passion,
with no looking back!

50
00:04:23,085 --> 00:04:24,609
If you work hard at it,

51
00:04:24,686 --> 00:04:28,520
I'm telling you, son,
you will become a fine Shinobi! Yay!

52
00:04:31,894 --> 00:04:34,454
<i>Who is he?</i>
<i>He is pretty overbearing.</i>

53
00:04:35,697 --> 00:04:39,258
Son, be ambitious! Bloom of Youth...

54
00:04:39,701 --> 00:04:42,226
Well then, adieu.

55
00:04:48,677 --> 00:04:51,646
<i>That was the first time I met Guy Sensei.</i>

56
00:04:52,514 --> 00:04:53,310
<i>And then...</i>

57
00:04:53,916 --> 00:04:57,147
Today, you have all become Genin.

58
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,782
I want to hear what
your goals are for the future.

59
00:05:06,161 --> 00:05:07,389
I don't want to answer.

60
00:05:08,597 --> 00:05:09,894
I-I...!

61
00:05:10,866 --> 00:05:13,391
I'd like to prove that
I could become a splendid Ninja,

62
00:05:13,635 --> 00:05:16,763
even though I can't use
Ninjutsu or Genjutsu!

63
00:05:17,539 --> 00:05:19,439
That would be the ultimate for me!

64
00:05:19,608 --> 00:05:20,905
<i>Those are good serious eyes...</i>

65
00:05:21,843 --> 00:05:23,834
You! What's so funny?!

66
00:05:24,079 --> 00:05:25,376
I'm serious!

67
00:05:25,447 --> 00:05:29,474
I will become a respectable Ninja
even only with Taijutsu!

68
00:05:29,685 --> 00:05:33,314
Don't you realize that
if you can't use Ninjutsu or Genjutsu,

69
00:05:33,388 --> 00:05:35,083
you're not a Ninja in the first place?

70
00:05:36,825 --> 00:05:39,316
Don't you remember being told
that you're the first person

71
00:05:39,394 --> 00:05:41,624
to graduate from the academy
who's only able to use Taijutsu?

72
00:05:42,264 --> 00:05:46,826
It's not because you're so good;
it's just that you're unusual.

73
00:05:46,902 --> 00:05:47,732
W-Why!

74
00:05:52,374 --> 00:05:56,538
Listen up! If you have passion,
it's not necessarily so.

75
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:03,777
If you act with passion,

76
00:06:03,852 --> 00:06:05,683
compete with good rivals
and lift each other up,

77
00:06:05,754 --> 00:06:07,813
you can all become great Ninja!

78
00:06:09,091 --> 00:06:10,353
But you know,
you have to work hard!

79
00:06:11,059 --> 00:06:12,117
<i>Passion...</i>

80
00:06:13,895 --> 00:06:16,523
<i>I...was inspired by Guy Sensei.</i>

81
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:20,328
<i>By his words...and his deeds.</i>

82
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:31,871
You're late!
17 minutes and 32 seconds late!

83
00:06:32,214 --> 00:06:34,011
Let's not do it today, all right?

84
00:06:34,583 --> 00:06:36,107
Each of us has 48 wins!

85
00:06:36,685 --> 00:06:38,778
With a win today,
one of us will pull ahead!

86
00:06:42,057 --> 00:06:44,321
I guess you won't give up
even if I say I wouldn't want to do it.

87
00:06:45,694 --> 00:06:48,993
It's my turn to choose the event, right?

88
00:06:49,197 --> 00:06:51,131
Right! What's it gonna be?

89
00:06:51,466 --> 00:06:53,627
A Taijutsu battle? A 100 meter dash?

90
00:06:53,702 --> 00:06:55,169
Holding our breath under water?

91
00:06:55,404 --> 00:06:57,235
I don't care, we could even
have an eating contest...

92
00:06:57,873 --> 00:06:58,897
Please...

93
00:07:10,018 --> 00:07:11,144
Okay, then...

94
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:13,254
Wh-What?!

95
00:07:15,757 --> 00:07:16,781
Rock, paper, scissors!

96
00:07:18,627 --> 00:07:20,788
Rock, paper, scissors?
That's what you choose?

97
00:07:20,862 --> 00:07:23,387
They say that your luck is
one part of your skill, don't they?

98
00:07:23,598 --> 00:07:28,126
Plus, it's a great competition
for testing your observational reflexes...

99
00:07:28,503 --> 00:07:30,300
R-Right.

100
00:07:30,972 --> 00:07:33,805
Do you get the feeling
Kakashi's just playing around with Guy

101
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:35,536
'cuz he can't be bothered?

102
00:07:35,877 --> 00:07:37,174
That's what it looks like to me.

103
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:40,748
I accept the battle.
There's no way I'm gonna lose!

104
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:45,750
If I do, I'll walk around the Leaf Village
500 times on my hands!

105
00:07:46,788 --> 00:07:48,153
There you go again...

106
00:07:48,924 --> 00:07:50,050
I promise!

107
00:07:50,692 --> 00:07:51,659
Here we go

108
00:07:51,727 --> 00:07:54,218
Another one of your special,
self-imposed rules.

109
00:07:54,730 --> 00:07:56,254
He can't do that.

110
00:07:56,331 --> 00:07:59,164
That's ridiculous.
He's acting like a kid.

111
00:08:00,202 --> 00:08:03,262
Yeah, that's impossible,
even for Guy Sensei.

112
00:08:03,705 --> 00:08:05,297
Impossible? Reckless, I'd say!

113
00:08:12,414 --> 00:08:13,881
- Rock, paper!
- Rock, paper!

114
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:18,877
Here you are.

115
00:08:21,223 --> 00:08:22,383
Guy Sensei?

116
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:24,417
How did you know I was here?

117
00:08:24,493 --> 00:08:26,927
I know everything about you.

118
00:08:31,566 --> 00:08:34,433
I heard that you skipped out
on rehabilitation these past two days?

119
00:08:34,803 --> 00:08:35,792
You can't be doing that!

120
00:08:45,647 --> 00:08:47,342
When I first became Genin...

121
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:51,883
this is where I revealed
my dream, my aspiration.

122
00:08:55,924 --> 00:09:01,021
Neji laughed at me then,
but I meant what I said.

123
00:09:03,832 --> 00:09:06,357
<i>I'd like to prove that</i>
<i>I could become a splendid Ninja</i>

124
00:09:06,735 --> 00:09:09,727
<i>even though I can't use</i>
<i>Ninjutsu or Genjutsu!</i>

125
00:09:10,505 --> 00:09:12,530
<i>That would be the ultimate for me!</i>

126
00:09:13,375 --> 00:09:16,242
At that time, you told me...

127
00:09:16,711 --> 00:09:18,872
If you act with passion,
compete with rivals,

128
00:09:19,347 --> 00:09:21,076
you can become a fine Ninja.

129
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:23,174
And that...

130
00:09:23,552 --> 00:09:25,816
In order to do that, it'd take "effort."

131
00:09:29,124 --> 00:09:30,216
I was happy to hear that.

132
00:09:31,893 --> 00:09:33,019
- Transform!
- Transform!

133
00:09:35,464 --> 00:09:36,829
Because while at the academy...

134
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:42,569
no one, not one friend or teacher,
said that kind of thing to me.

135
00:09:50,412 --> 00:09:52,243
You put me at ease...

136
00:09:53,348 --> 00:09:57,148
You opened up a path
just when I was unsure of myself.

137
00:09:57,886 --> 00:10:01,014
I realized all I had to do
was try my best.

138
00:10:13,068 --> 00:10:15,036
And when I complained that

139
00:10:15,103 --> 00:10:18,300
all my efforts couldn't match
the others natural talents,

140
00:10:18,373 --> 00:10:21,604
you told me that I had
a natural talent for effort.

141
00:10:22,911 --> 00:10:28,247
That was when I learned the importance
of believing in my own strength.

142
00:10:33,221 --> 00:10:38,022
<i>The chance of a successful surgery</i>
<i>is probably 50%, at best.</i>

143
00:10:44,099 --> 00:10:48,968
But... this is one time...
even if I try my best...!

144
00:10:49,037 --> 00:10:53,371
And even if I believe in myself,
there's nothing in the world I can do!

145
00:10:56,511 --> 00:10:59,742
Guy Sensei... Please tell me...!

146
00:11:03,518 --> 00:11:07,545
<i>Please tell me.</i>
<i>Can I become like you?</i>

147
00:11:08,523 --> 00:11:11,390
Why did this kind of thing
happen only to me?

148
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:14,028
<i>Because I have my own</i>
<i>Way of Ninja to follow,</i>

149
00:11:14,095 --> 00:11:16,655
<i>my own dreams and aspirations</i>
<i>that I have to protect and</i>

150
00:11:16,731 --> 00:11:19,165
<i>prove to the world even</i>
<i>if it means dying for...</i>

151
00:11:19,401 --> 00:11:21,767
What should I do?!

152
00:11:22,637 --> 00:11:24,070
<i>The Eight Inner Gates...</i>

153
00:11:24,506 --> 00:11:27,202
<i>Is this the Forbidden Jutsu that</i>
<i>will destroy the body of the practitioner?</i>

154
00:11:28,143 --> 00:11:29,508
Please tell me!

155
00:11:30,512 --> 00:11:31,911
<i>I'm prepared for the worst.</i>

156
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:34,205
<i>Please teach me that Forbidden Jutsu!</i>

157
00:11:34,482 --> 00:11:36,074
<i>Everything is...for my dream!</i>

158
00:11:39,321 --> 00:11:41,482
<i>That means everything to me!</i>

159
00:11:54,236 --> 00:11:57,501
<i>You tried to become a great Ninja</i>
<i>relying only on Taijutsu...</i>

160
00:11:58,474 --> 00:12:00,738
<i>Until now, that's all you had.</i>

161
00:12:04,046 --> 00:12:05,308
<i>It must be so painful for you...</i>

162
00:12:05,514 --> 00:12:07,379
<i>Now that it seems that your dreams</i>

163
00:12:07,549 --> 00:12:09,779
<i>and all your wishes</i>
<i>are being cruelly taken away.</i>

164
00:12:12,254 --> 00:12:16,247
<i>It does not matter what his wishes are,</i>
<i>he should give up on becoming a Shinobi.</i>

165
00:12:20,129 --> 00:12:21,096
Lee...

166
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:30,261
If you want to be free of that pain,
you have to prepare yourself!

167
00:12:35,611 --> 00:12:39,206
Does it mean...
to prepare to give up my dreams?

168
00:12:39,982 --> 00:12:41,779
If you lose your dreams,

169
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:44,250
you will undergo pain even greater
than what you feel now.

170
00:12:45,788 --> 00:12:49,690
Neither you nor I would be able to
go on living if we lose the Way of Ninja.

171
00:12:50,359 --> 00:12:52,259
What fools we are...

172
00:12:55,931 --> 00:12:58,195
Lee! Have the surgeny!

173
00:13:18,387 --> 00:13:21,379
How's it going with Cell Activation Jutsu?

174
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,623
It's all about the Chakra, but...

175
00:13:25,394 --> 00:13:26,656
There are so many kinds of cells...

176
00:13:26,729 --> 00:13:29,630
skin cells, internal organ cells,
muscular cells...

177
00:13:30,332 --> 00:13:34,393
You know, it's just a tad difficult
to activate all of them at once.

178
00:13:34,536 --> 00:13:37,232
What's that?
"Just a tad," you say?

179
00:13:38,574 --> 00:13:40,166
Are you testing me?

180
00:13:40,242 --> 00:13:41,368
Oh no!

181
00:13:43,245 --> 00:13:45,304
I'm declaring my trust in you.

182
00:14:03,165 --> 00:14:05,360
I don't know why,
but just a while ago...

183
00:14:05,434 --> 00:14:07,197
I was remembering the time
when you and Kakashi Sensei

184
00:14:07,269 --> 00:14:11,103
were competing
with rock, paper, scissors.

185
00:14:12,074 --> 00:14:13,598
At that time, Kakashi Sensei said

186
00:14:13,675 --> 00:14:16,576
that your luck is
one part of your skill, right?

187
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:22,517
This surgery is also fifty fifty,
live or die...

188
00:14:23,519 --> 00:14:24,281
But...

189
00:14:25,187 --> 00:14:26,779
it's not a game of
rock, paper, scissors!

190
00:14:29,892 --> 00:14:33,692
Do you remember what happened
after that, Lee?

191
00:14:42,204 --> 00:14:45,662
500 times around...
It's a promise! Yay!

192
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:49,099
What's he doing?!

193
00:15:16,138 --> 00:15:17,127
Shoot!

194
00:15:22,644 --> 00:15:26,910
<i>If I lose, I'll walk 500 times</i>
<i>around the Leaf Village, on my hands!</i>

195
00:15:27,583 --> 00:15:28,447
<i>It's a promise!</i>

196
00:15:29,284 --> 00:15:33,812
<i>He can't do that! That's stupid.</i>
<i>He's acting like a kid.</i>

197
00:15:46,435 --> 00:15:47,834
Hah! This is nothing.

198
00:15:57,679 --> 00:16:00,512
Wh-What are you doing here, Lee?

199
00:16:01,383 --> 00:16:02,281
Why are you doing this?

200
00:16:02,951 --> 00:16:07,081
Kakashi Sensei is not here.
In fact, <i>no one</i> is watching.

201
00:16:08,624 --> 00:16:10,717
When a man stands cool with
a Nice guy pose in front of others,

202
00:16:10,792 --> 00:16:14,819
he should keep his promise,
even if it kills him!

203
00:16:16,999 --> 00:16:18,523
<i>It's a promise!</i>

204
00:16:22,871 --> 00:16:23,769
What?

205
00:16:24,573 --> 00:16:26,768
Why do you always do that?

206
00:16:26,975 --> 00:16:28,272
Whenever you're about to start
doing something,

207
00:16:28,343 --> 00:16:30,004
why do you always come up
with some kind of crazy rule.

208
00:16:34,616 --> 00:16:36,413
Good question, Lee.

209
00:16:36,618 --> 00:16:40,145
You really know how
to get to the point.

210
00:16:40,522 --> 00:16:44,618
OK, I'll tell you.
But remember, you can't tell anyone else.

211
00:16:45,494 --> 00:16:46,358
What's the answer?

212
00:16:46,662 --> 00:16:52,362
Making self-rules is nothing less than
a practice which brings me victory!

213
00:16:55,204 --> 00:16:56,831
S-Self-rules...?

214
00:16:57,306 --> 00:16:58,170
Are you ready?

215
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:01,876
The point of these rules is that,
when you're going after something,

216
00:17:01,944 --> 00:17:04,879
they push you into a real tough spot...

217
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:07,105
It's about chaining yourself down.

218
00:17:07,482 --> 00:17:10,144
For example, on the other side
of the hellish rule that

219
00:17:10,219 --> 00:17:12,949
"If I lose at rock, scissors, paper,
I'll do 500 laps" is the idea that

220
00:17:13,055 --> 00:17:14,317
"If I do 500 laps,

221
00:17:14,389 --> 00:17:17,449
there's no way I won't be able
to beat Kakashi next time.

222
00:17:17,526 --> 00:17:20,256
They hold power,
the potential of the heavens.

223
00:17:20,729 --> 00:17:21,753
Y-Yes...

224
00:17:22,297 --> 00:17:25,926
By being chained down
to doing 500 laps,

225
00:17:26,001 --> 00:17:29,164
it makes you get serious.

226
00:17:29,238 --> 00:17:32,469
Even about things like
rock, paper, scissors competitions,

227
00:17:32,541 --> 00:17:34,202
which are so trifling otherwise.

228
00:17:35,477 --> 00:17:39,641
And, even if you lose,
walking around the village 500 times

229
00:17:39,715 --> 00:17:43,845
gives you the benefit
of extremely intense training.

230
00:17:45,254 --> 00:17:46,346
I see!

231
00:17:47,122 --> 00:17:49,818
OK, I've gotta do a little more.
Here we go!

232
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:53,151
I'm going with you!
I have my own "self-rule" which is...

233
00:17:53,729 --> 00:17:56,323
Hey! Hey! Don't push yourself, Lee.

234
00:17:56,698 --> 00:17:59,394
If I can't keep up with you, I'll...

235
00:18:00,035 --> 00:18:02,629
try even harder!

236
00:18:04,406 --> 00:18:06,340
That is, I'll aim to be like you.

237
00:18:06,575 --> 00:18:11,069
And if I keep trying,
I'll be able to become a great Ninja!

238
00:18:13,982 --> 00:18:17,179
All right! If that's the case,
then I have an addition to my rule!

239
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:22,083
If you can't keep up with me
all the way to the end...

240
00:18:22,557 --> 00:18:25,617
I'll put every ounce of
my being into training you!

241
00:18:27,262 --> 00:18:31,699
If I train you with all my being,
you'll be able to turn into a fine Ninja!

242
00:18:32,834 --> 00:18:33,766
I promise!

243
00:18:40,442 --> 00:18:42,706
Huh, that's right.

244
00:18:43,712 --> 00:18:47,512
That was the first time you told me about
the "self-rule," wasn't it?

245
00:18:49,418 --> 00:18:50,976
Your surgery will be a success

246
00:18:51,053 --> 00:18:53,817
because you have worked hard
all the way through.

247
00:18:54,856 --> 00:18:57,723
You have the power to bring
your own future in the heavens.

248
00:18:58,694 --> 00:18:59,854
And in the one in a thousand...

249
00:18:59,928 --> 00:19:03,329
no, one in a million chance
that something goes wrong...

250
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:07,032
I will die with you!

251
00:19:14,076 --> 00:19:15,441
Ever since I met you,

252
00:19:15,844 --> 00:19:20,178
my Way of Ninja has been to
nurture you into a fine Ninja.

253
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,308
I promise you!

254
00:19:27,656 --> 00:19:32,218
<i>Neither you nor I would be able</i>
<i>to go on living if we lose the Way of Ninja.</i>

255
00:19:32,728 --> 00:19:34,855
<i>What fools we are...</i>

256
00:19:39,634 --> 00:19:42,194
G-Guy Sensei!

257
00:19:53,849 --> 00:19:55,942
OK, let's go, Lee!

258
00:19:56,151 --> 00:19:57,243
Yes, sir!

259
00:20:17,806 --> 00:20:18,704
Lady Tsunade!

260
00:20:41,563 --> 00:20:43,087
From this day forward,

261
00:20:43,165 --> 00:20:47,158
I am the ruler of the Village Hidden
in the Leaves, the Fifth Hokage!

262
00:21:06,788 --> 00:21:11,487
<i>I believe your promise,</i>
<i>its a true heart give me courage</i>

263
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:15,894
<i>Always I feel it</i>
<i>the precious time with you</i>

264
00:21:16,498 --> 00:21:20,025
<i>On your still shoulder</i>

265
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:25,730
<i>I feel the wind that blows</i>
<i>towards tomorrow</i>

266
00:21:25,908 --> 00:21:31,346
<i>The city lights are like pieces of stars</i>

267
00:21:31,847 --> 00:21:36,147
<i>That hold us together</i>

268
00:21:36,618 --> 00:21:45,856
<i>"Each one of us glows differently,"</i>

269
00:21:45,928 --> 00:21:48,522
<i>you say laughingly</i>

270
00:21:48,764 --> 00:21:54,430
<i>but you look most dazzling</i>

271
00:21:55,003 --> 00:21:59,372
<i>Like a comet,</i>

272
00:21:59,441 --> 00:22:05,539
<i>like the rainbow after the storm</i>

273
00:22:05,614 --> 00:22:12,713
<i>You bring light into my heart</i>

274
00:22:13,722 --> 00:22:23,097
<i>Being lost can be the answer</i>

275
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:31,965
<i>Let's promise we won't cheat</i>

276
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:36,033
<i>Uh...like a shooting star,</i>
<i>we do go ahead.</i>

277
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:40,707
Darn! He has no hole
in his defense.

278
00:22:40,782 --> 00:22:42,545
Being impatient won't
do any good, Naruto.

279
00:22:42,618 --> 00:22:44,017
Let's utilize the next mission.

280
00:22:44,186 --> 00:22:46,654
That's right. The next mission
requires an overnight stay.

281
00:22:46,855 --> 00:22:49,119
- Our chance will be at the inn.
- Roger that!

282
00:22:49,191 --> 00:22:51,625
Once we get to the inn,
we'll wait until he's defenseless...

283
00:22:51,827 --> 00:22:53,385
- and then...
- and then...

284
00:22:53,629 --> 00:22:55,187
- unmask him at once!
- Unmask him at once!

285
00:22:55,764 --> 00:23:00,861
Next time: "Gotta See! Gotta Know!
Kakashi Sensei's True Face!"

286
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:04,068
'Cuz we're really curious!
